results.name: Number of divisors of n-th refactorable number (A033950(n)).
comment: A number n is refactorable if the number of divisors of n divides n.
link: Amiram Eldar, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
mathematica: fQ[n_] := Mod[n, DivisorSigma[0, n]] == 0; DivisorSigma[0, # ] & /@ Select[ Range[1000], fQ[ # ] &] (* _Robert G. Wilson v_ *)
program: (MAGMA) v:=[ n: n in [1..900] | n mod NumberOfDivisors(n) eq 0 ]; [NumberOfDivisors(v[i]): i in [1..#v]]; // _Marius A. Burtea_, Jul 02 2019
